The paper deals with algorithms for testing whether a choice function induced by a preference list is substitutable. This is a problem in computational social choice, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The use of preference lists and choice functions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The running time of the algorithms involves the size of the universe and the length of the preference list, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
